trans-unit.source: ApcuEngine - Uses the APCu object cache, one of the fastest caching engines.
ArrayEngine - Uses only memory to store all data, not actually a persistent engine. Can be useful in test or CLI environment.

Auth.afterIdentify - Fired after a user has been identified using one of configured authenticate class. The callback function should have signature like afterIdentify(Event $event, array $user) when $user is the identified user record.
Auth.logout - Fired when AuthComponent::logout() is called. The callback function should have signature like logout(Event $event, array $user) where $user is the user about to be logged out.
BUILD_VALIDATOR_EVENT - The name of the event to be triggred when validators are built.
False to remove current plugin name is deprecated as of 3.4.0. Use directly null instead.
False to remove current theme is deprecated as of 3.4.0. Use directly null instead.

FileEngine - Uses simple files to store content. Poor performance, but good for storing large objects, or things that are not IO sensitive. Well suited to development as it is an easy cache to inspect and manually flush.
Foo Matches any key with the exact same value.

Hash provides an improved interface, more consistent and predictable set of features over Set. While it lacks the spotty support for pseudo Xpath, its more fully featured dot notation provides similar features in a more consistent implementation.
Mdy December 27, 2006 or Dec 27, 2006 comma is optional
MemcacheEngine - Uses the PECL::Memcache extension and Memcached for storage. Fast reads/writes, and benefits from memcache being distributed.
Model.afterDelete Fired after the delete has been successful. Receives the event, entity, and options.
Model.afterDeleteCommit Fired after the transaction is committed for an atomic delete. Receives the event, entity, and options.
Model.beforeDelete Fired before the delete occurs. If stopped the delete will be aborted. Receives the event, entity, and options.
RedisEngine - Uses redis and php-redis extension to store cache data.
Router::url('/posts/edit/1'); Returns the string with the base dir prepended. This usage does not use reverser routing.
Router::url(['_name' => 'custom-name', ...]); Returns a URL generated through reverse routing. This form allows you to leverage named routes.
Router::url(['controller' => 'posts', 'action' => 'edit']); Returns a URL generated through reverse routing.
VALIDATOR_PROVIDER_NAME - The provider name the including class is assigned in validators.
WincacheEngine - Uses Windows Cache Extension for PHP. Supports wincache 1.1.0 and higher. This engine is recommended to people deploying on windows with IIS.
XcacheEngine - Uses the Xcache extension, an alternative to APCu.

_base - Set to false to remove the base path from the generated URL. If your application is not in the root directory, this can be used to generate URLs that are 'cake relative'. cake relative URLs are required when using requestAction.
_ext - Defines the extensions used for this route.
_ext is an array of filename extensions that will be parsed out of the url if present. See \Cake\Routing\RouteCollection::setExtensions().
_full - If true output of Router::fullBaseUrl() will be prepended to generated URLs.

_host - Define the host name pattern if you want this route to only match specific host names. You can use .* and to create wildcard subdomains/hosts e.g. *.example.com matches all subdomains on example.com.
_host - Set the host to use for the link. Defaults to the current host.
_jsonOptions You can set custom options for json_encode() this way, e.g. JSON_HEX_TAG | JSON_HEX_APOS.
_method Only match requests with specific HTTP verbs.
_middleware - Define the middleware names for this route.
_name - Name of route. If you have setup named routes you can use this key to specify it.
_name is used to define a specific name for routes. This can be used to optimize reverse routing lookups. If undefined a name will be generated for each connected route.
_port - Set the port if you need to create links on non-standard ports.
_scheme - Set to create links on different schemes like webcal or ftp. Defaults to the current scheme.

_serialize To convert a set of view variables into a JSON response. Its value can be a string for single variable name or array for multiple names. If true all view variables will be serialized. It unset normal view template will be rendered. _jsonp Enables JSONP support and wraps response in callback function provided in query string. - Setting it to true enables the default query string parameter "callback". - Setting it to a string value, uses the provided query string parameter for finding the JSONP callback name.

_serialize To convert a set of view variables into a serialized form. Its value can be a string for single variable name or array for multiple names. If true all view variables will be serialized. If unset normal view template will be rendered.
_ssl - Set to true to convert the generated URL to https, or false to force http.
_xmlOptions You can set an array of custom options for Xml::fromArray() this way, e.g. 'format' as 'attributes' instead of 'tags'.
absoluteString => The printf compatible string when outputting absolute time
absoluteString => The printf compatible string when outputting absolute date
absoluteString => The printf compatible string when outputting absolute time
accuracy => Specifies how accurate the date should be described (array)
action The controller action the form submits to, (optional). Use this option if you don't need to change the controller from the current request's controller. Deprecated since 3.2, use url.
after - Text to display after the rendered number
after - The string to place after decimal numbers, e.g. ']'
after Content to be inserted after the numbers, but before the last links.
afterDelete(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options) Fired after an entity has been deleted.
afterFilter(Event $event) Called after each action is complete and after the view is rendered.
afterLayout(Event $event, $layoutFile) - afterLayout is called after the layout has rendered.
afterRender(Event $event, $viewFile) - afterRender is called after the view file is rendered but before the layout has been rendered.
afterRenderFile(Event $event, $viewFile, $content) - Called after any view fragment is rendered. If a listener returns a non-null value, the output of the rendered file will be set to that.

afterRules(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options, bool $result, $operation) Fired after the rules have been checked on the entity. By stopping this event, you can return the final value of the rules checking operation.

afterRules(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options, bool $result, string $operation) Fired after the rules have been checked on the entity. By stopping this event, you can return the final value of the rules checking operation.
afterSave(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options) Fired after an entity is saved.

afterSaveCommit(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options) Fired after the transaction in which the save operation is wrapped has been committed. It’s also triggered for non atomic saves where database operations are implicitly committed. The event is triggered only for the primary table on which save() is directly called. The event is not triggered if a transaction is started before calling save.
allowMultipleNulls Set to false to disallow multiple null values in multi-column unique rules. By default this is true to emulate how SQL UNIQUE keys work.
allowedActions - Actions from which actions of the current controller are allowed to receive requests.
allowedControllers - Controllers from which actions of the current controller are allowed to receive requests.
args - Should arguments for functions be shown? If true, the arguments for each method call will be displayed.
array Array with 2 indexes. 0 => plugin name, 1 => class name.
associative - A list of properties that should be treated as associative arrays. Properties in this list will be passed through Hash::normalize() before merging.
atomic Defaults to true. When true the deletion happens within a transaction.
authError - Error to display when user attempts to access an object or action to which they do not have access.
authenticate - An array of authentication objects to use for authenticating users. You can configure multiple adapters and they will be checked sequentially when users are identified.
authorize - An array of authorization objects to use for authorizing users. You can configure multiple adapters and they will be checked sequentially when authorization checks are done.

autoload - boolean - Whether or not you want an autoloader registered. This defaults to false. The framework assumes you have configured autoloaders using composer. However, if your application source tree is made up of plugins, this can be a useful option.
base The base URL for the request.
before - Text to display before the rendered number
before - The string to place before whole numbers, e.g. '['
before Content to be inserted before the numbers, but after the first links.
beforeDelete(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options) Fired before an entity is deleted. By stopping this event you will abort the delete operation.
beforeFilter(Event $event) Called before each action. This is a good place to do general logic that applies to all actions.
beforeFilter(Event $event) Called before the controller's beforeFilter method by default.

beforeFind(Event $event, Query $query, ArrayObject $options, boolean $primary) Fired before each find operation. By stopping the event and supplying a return value you can bypass the find operation entirely. Any changes done to the $query instance will be retained for the rest of the find. The $primary parameter indicates whether or not this is the root query, or an associated query.

beforeRedirect(Event $event $url, Response $response) Called before a redirect is done. Allows you to change the URL that will be redirected to by returning a Response instance with new URL set using Response::location(). Redirection can be prevented by stopping the event propagation.
beforeRedirect(Event $event, $url, Response $response) Called before a redirect is done.
beforeRender(Event $event) Called before the Controller beforeRender, and before the view class is loaded.
beforeRender(Event $event) Called before the view is rendered.
beforeRender(Event $event, $viewFile) - beforeRender is called before the view file is rendered.
beforeRenderFile(Event $event, $viewFile) - Called before any view fragment is rendered.

beforeRules(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options, $operation) Fired before an entity is validated using by a rules checker. By stopping this event, you can return the final value of the rules checking operation.

beforeRules(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options, string $operation) Fired before an entity is validated using the rules checker. By stopping this event, you can return the final value of the rules checking operation.

beforeSave(Event $event, EntityInterface $entity, ArrayObject $options) Fired before each entity is saved. Stopping this event will abort the save operation. When the event is stopped the result of the event will be returned.
blackHoleCallback - The controller method that will be called if this request is black-hole'd.
block - Set to true to append form to view block "postLink" or provide custom block name.
block - Set to true to append output to view block "meta" or provide custom block name.
block Set to true to append output to view block "css" or provide custom block name.
block Set to true to append output to view block "script" or provide custom block name.
block The block name to append the output to, or false/absent to return as a string

boolean - The option uses no value, it's just a boolean switch. Defaults to false. If an option is defined as boolean, it will always be added to the parsed params. If no present it will be false, if present it will be true.
bootstrap - array - Whether or not you want the $plugin/config/bootstrap.php file loaded.
buildRules(Event $event, RulesChecker $rules) Allows listeners to modify the rules checker by adding more rules.
buildRules(Event $event, RulesChecker $rules) Fired when the rules checking object for the table is being built. You can use this callback to add more rules to the set.
buildValidator(Event $event, Validator $validator, string $name) Allows listeners to modify validation rules for the provided named validator.

buildValidator(Event $event, Validator $validator, string $name) Fired when the validator object identified by $name is being built. You can use this callback to add validation rules or add validation providers.
callback The callback that will be called in a loop to advance the progress bar.

checkAuthIn - Name of event for which initial auth checks should be done. Defaults to 'Controller.startup'. You can set it to 'Controller.initialize' if you want the check to be done before controller's beforeFilter() is run.
checkHttpCache - Whether to check for HTTP cache.
checkRules Defaults to true. Check deletion rules before deleting the record.
checkbox Renders checkbox input controls. Accepts the name, value and attrs variables.
checkboxWrapper Renders the containing div/element for a checkbox and its label. Accepts the input, and label variables.
checked - boolean indicate that this checkbox is checked.
children The key name to use in the resultset for children.
chmod The mode to copy the files/directories with.
choices A list of valid choices for this argument. If left empty all values are valid.. An exception will be raised when parse() encounters an invalid value.
choices A list of valid choices for this option. If left empty all values are valid.. An exception will be raised when parse() encounters an invalid value.
class - The class name to use, defaults to time-ago-in-words.
class - When using multiple = checkbox the class name to apply to the divs. Defaults to 'checkbox'.
classBase - The path relative to path which contains the folders with class files. Defaults to "src".

className Define the specific class name to use. If undefined, CakePHP will generate the class name based on the alias. For example 'Users' would result in App\Model\Table\UsersTable being used. If this class does not exist, then the default Cake\ORM\Table class will be used. By setting the className option you can define the specific class to use. The className option supports plugin short class references Cake\Core\App::shortName().
clear A bool stating if the current stack should be cleared to start a new one
confirm - Confirm message to show. Form execution will only continue if confirmed then.
connection Inject the specific connection object to use. If this option and connectionName are undefined, The table class' defaultConnectionName() method will be invoked to fetch the connection name.
connectionName Define the connection name to use. The named connection will be fetched from Cake\Datasource\ConnectionManager.
context Additional options for the context class. For example the EntityContext accepts a 'table' option that allows you to set the specific Table class the form should be based on.
cookieName The name of the cookie to send.
data - Array with key/value to pass in input hidden
database database number to use for connection.
day - Array of options for the day select box.
default - Set the default value for the checkbox. This allows you to start checkboxes as checked, without having to check the POST data. A matching POST data value, will overwrite the default value.

default - The default value for this option. Defaults are added into the parsed params when the attached option is not provided or has no value. Using default and boolean together will not work. are added into the parsed parameters when the option is undefined. Defaults to null.
default - mixed - The value to use if there is no value in the form's context.
default The default value of the column.
default: Default value to return if no value found in request data or context record.
defaults The default values for fields. These values will be used when there is no request data set. Data should be nested following the dot separated paths you access your fields with.
delete The behavior on delete. Options are 'restrict', 'setNull', 'cascade', 'noAction'.
depth - The number of stack frames to return. Defaults to 999
direction The default direction to use when this link isn't active.
disabled - Control the disabled attribute. When creating a select box, set to true to disable the select box. Set to an array to disable specific option elements.
disabled - Control the disabled attribute. When creating checkboxes, true will disable all checkboxes. You can also set disabled to a list of values you want to disable when creating checkboxes.
disabled - Either true or an array of inputs to disable. When true, the select element will be disabled.
disabled - Either true or an array of options to disable.
disabled - Either true or an array of options to disable. When true, the select element will be disabled.
disabled - Set to true or disabled to disable all the radio buttons. Use an array of values to disable specific radio buttons.
disabled - Whether or not the checkbox should be disabled.
disabled - mixed - Either a boolean indicating disabled state, or the string in a numerically indexed value.
disabled Either a boolean or an array of checkboxes to disable.
